    image black 1: There are a great many different species of plants, nearly enough to rival the greenhouse. There are even a few that you don't remember seeing there.
    
    // You would know, with the amount of time you've spent sneaking around to perform your duties while avoiding Professor Delta's antics.
    
    * *     (allergy) You are allergic to one[] of these flowers. You recall a time long ago, very long ago, when you were far younger and even less observant.
    
            That flower is pain, to you. The pain is the only real fragment of the memory left, the rest a burned-out hole where the flower ate its way through.
            
            Even existing within a few meters of it is enough to make your skin crawl. Whether this is a psycho- or physiological reaction is not something you care to find out.
            
            You step away from the awful thing.
            
            Discomfort is not the only reason you avoid it. To know this about this quality of yours would expose others to more about your past than you could bear. 
            
            Nobody, especially not the committee, must ever know why it came to be that you entered Sakura Secondary.
            
            You create distance between yourself and the singularly painful plant with the utmost discretion, lest Plume observe 
            
    * *     (scary) One [is scary] carries with it an awful appearance and, to your mind, horrific baggage.
    
            Perhaps you had once thought it beautiful. Perhaps it <i>is</> beautiful. 
            
            You would not know, as it has only been a symbol of a singular nightmare for as long as you can remember.
            
            It takes everything in you not to sprint over and snip it with something painful and dull and throw it into one of the nearby chimneys.
            
            Even that fate would be too good for it.
            
            Besides, Plume might notice, 
    
    * *     (lovely) One is [beautiful] overwhelmingly beautiful. It's a flower you know very well, and have a special connection to. 
    
            Many others have strong opinions on it either way. You know where you stand.
            
            It would be extremely hard to guess how much you care for it, and you've played your cards close to your chest so far.
            
            Perhaps you should open up, a little? 
            
            Bare your heart, or at least become vulnerable enough for someone to get the hint.
            
            It would be nice, if Ananas was right about the tradition, for someone to bring it to you. It would be proof that you are in the right place. 
            
            That coming here was not a mistake.
            
            ...
            
            You have played your cards close for a reason.
            
            They will not know why you came here.
            
            They must not know, and thus they must not know your flower.
            
            ...
            
            Even so, you look at it for longer than you had planned. You tear yourself away quickly, lest Plume notice
